import eptstgcn
import torch
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import gc
# url0 = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pinkocto/noteda/main/posts/SOLAR/data4/stgcn_data0.json"
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pinkocto/noteda/main/posts/SOLAR/data2/stgcn_data1.json"
url2 = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pinkocto/noteda/main/posts/SOLAR/data4/stgcn_data2.json"
# loader0 = eptstgcn.DatasetLoader0(url0)
loader = eptstgcn.DatasetLoader(url)
loader2 = eptstgcn.DatasetLoader(url2)
# dataset0 = loader0.get_dataset(lags=1)
dataset = loader.get_dataset(lags=24)
dataset2 = loader2.get_dataset(lags=24)
# train_dataset0, test_dataset0 = eptstgcn.utils.temporal_signal_split(dataset0, train_ratio = 0.7)
train_dataset, test_dataset = eptstgcn.utils.temporal_signal_split(dataset, train_ratio = 0.7)
train_dataset2, test_dataset2 = eptstgcn.utils.temporal_signal_split(dataset2, train_ratio = 0.7)
lrnr1 = eptstgcn.StgcnLearner(train_dataset, dataset_name = '(2022/06/01 ~ 2022/09/15)')
# evtor1 = eptstgcn.Evaluator(lrnr1, train_dataset1, test_dataset1)
lrnr1.learn(filters=1, epoch=10)
10/10
evtor1 = eptstgcn.Evaluator(lrnr1, train_dataset, test_dataset)
# evtor0.tr_plot
# evtor1.test_plot(t=30)
# import pickle
# file_path = './lrnr_model/LRNR/'

# import pickle 
# with open(file_path + 'lrnr0_30epoch.pickle','wb') as fw:
#     pickle.dump(lrnr0, fw)
# lrnr = eptstgcn.StgcnLearner(train_dataset, dataset_name = 'corr (2022/06/01 ~ 2022/09/15)')
lrnr2 = eptstgcn.StgcnLearner(train_dataset2, dataset_name = 'ept-corr (2022/06/01 ~ 2022/09/15)')
lrnr2.learn(filters=4, epoch=30)
evtor2 = eptstgcn.Evaluator(lrnr2, train_dataset2, test_dataset2)
30/30
